    "description": {
      "en": {
        "provenance": "imported",
        "value": "In disaster situations, adolescent girls and young women are among the most vulnerable and hence, there is a need for targeted interventions, especially to support their learning. The project will strengthen the capacity of CLCs with regard to supporting learning in pre-, during and post-disaster situation and also providing livelihood support and Skill based training programme to the affected communities. The capacity of government officials at all levels and local stakeholders will also be enhanced with regard to delivery of quality education in the federal system, considering the social inclusion agenda - especially disadvantaged girls and women."
      },
